🖼️ Image to Code/Text Converter using OCR (Python + Tesseract)
This project extracts code or text from an image using Tesseract OCR and saves it into a .txt file (e.g., img_converted.txt).

✅ Features
Extracts code/text from any image (PNG, JPG, etc.)

Automatically saves the result to a .txt file

Works in any Python environment (VS Code, PyCharm, IDLE)

🚀 Installation & Setup
🔧 1. Install Python Dependencies

pip install pytesseract pillow
pytesseract is a Python wrapper for Google’s Tesseract-OCR engine
Pillow is used to handle images

📥 2. Install Tesseract OCR Engine
🔹 Windows:
Download installer from:
https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki

Run the installer:

✅ Select English language

✅ Check Add to system PATH

Install to: C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR\

Verify it works (in terminal):


tesseract --version

🔁 3. Set Path in Python (Only for Windows)
Add this in your Python script if Tesseract is not in PATH:

pytesseract.pytesseract.tesseract_cmd = r"C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR\tesseract.exe"
📂 Project Structure

├── image.png               # Image to extract from
├── img_converted.txt       # Output file (created after run)
├── ocr_script.py           # Python script to run
